 and the united states as of  february  over  million active users used avgs software products and services which include internet security performance optimization and personal privacy and identity protection applications in july  avast software announced that it intends to acquire avg the acquisition was completed on september   and avast and avg operate as a single company since october   retaining the two separate brands contents  history  products  multiplatform windows android mac  android security  productivity  mac security  productivity  privacy  business security  partnerships  controversy  references  external links historyedit company was founded in brno czech republic by jan gritzbach and tomáš hofer in  as grisoft c software spol s r o it was owned by jan gritzbach in  jan gritzbach decided to sell grisoft to benson oak capital acquisitions holding company grisoft inc based in wilmington delaware was used for the transaction in  the company was renamed to grisoft sro three years later benson oak sold a  share in the company to intel capital and enterprise investors for us million holding company was grisoft holdings bv based in amsterdam netherlands later grisoft international bv that gradually became the main company on  april  grisoft acquired the german company ewido networks an antispyware software manufacturer and incorporated ewidos features into new versions of avg software on  november  microsoft announced that avg security products would be available directly from the windows security center in windows vista since  june  the avg software has also been used as an optional component of gfi mailsecurity produced by gfi software on  december  grisoft announced the acquisition of exploit prevention labs developer of the linkscanner safe surfing technology in  grisoft sro was renamed to avg technologies cz sro and grisoft international bv to avg technologies nv this change was made to increase the effectiveness of their marketing activities in january  avg announced their plans to acquire sana security were finalized plans to integrate sanas technologies in their free consumer product avg antivirus are still under consideration according to jr smith avgs chief executive sana securitys developed technologies are currently licensed to symantec on  october  ta associates announced that they bought a minority stake in avg technologies for more than us million on april  avg announced the appointed of security industry veteran yuval benitzhak as senior vice president of engineering benitzhak became the chief technology officer later that year on  june  avg announced the acquisition of north carolinabased walling data a north america security software distribution that has distributed avg offerings across the united states since  on  november  avg announced the acquisition of tel avivbased droidsecurity a company that specializes in the field of mobile security solutions for android devices upon completion of the acquisition droidsecurity will become a wholly owned subsidiary of avg and droidsecurity ceo and cofounder eran pfeffer will become the general manager of avg’s mobile solutions team in december  avg released a mandatoryinstall update to the  version of its antivirus software which caused thousands of  bit windows vista and windows  computers to become completely inoperable avg has since released a fix which attempts to repair computers bricked after installing the update affected users can watch the following video on avgs official youtube page to resolve the issue on  january  a dangerous rogue appeared the interface and graphics resemble the previous version of the software and uses sophisticated social engineering to deceive users and infect their systems the malware also contains the internet explorer emergency mode on  december  avg technologies announced its acquisition of bsecure technologies inc bsecure a leading provider of proprietary cloudbased technology in the internet filtering industry since  and the most endorsed software provider for family online safety in  the group was restructured again avg technologies holdings bv was founded having avg technologies cz sro and avg technologies nv as its subsidiaries on  february  avg technologies nv was listed on new york stock exchange on  june  avg technologies announced the acquisition of level platforms march   jr smith ceo tendered his resignation from avg after eight years as ceo and leading the company to a successful ipo on the nyse and delivering eight quarters of successive highgrowth on  july  avg technologies announced gary kovacs as the companys new ceo in november  avg technologies announced the acquisition of norman safeground asa an oslobased company known for their norman suite of security products avg technologies announced in may  the acquisition of privax a uk based company which is an owner of hidemyass vpn service in september  the company announced the acquisition of location labs a company with personal security products on all four major us cellular carriers on  july  avast software announced that it intended to acquire avg technologies for a purchase price of  per share in cash for a total of around  billion the acquisition was completed on september   and avast and avg operate as a single company as of monday october   the company was delisted from the new york stock exchange productsedit main article avg software multiplatform windows android macedit avg antivirus free avg internet security avg tuneup avg driver updater avg ultimate android security  productivityedit avg antivirus for android avg cleaner for android family products of avgs location labs att smart limits att familymap verizon familybase tmobile familywhere sprint family locator sprint mobile controls mac security  productivityedit avg antivirus for mac avg cleaner for mac privacyedit hma pro vpn avg web tuneup business securityedit avg business cloudcare avg business managed workplace avg business sso secure single sign on avg antivirus business edition – an antivirus program with central administration capabilities avg internet security business edition – a business security suite with central administration capabilities avg file server business edition avg email server business edition avg pc tuneup business edition partnershipsedit on  august  avg entered into partnership with moka to secure desktop virtualisation solutions the partnership adds a critical security layer to the virtual desktop marketplace as more enterprise companies are turning to desktop virtualization as a secure solution for bringing your own computer byoc and work from home initiatives for employees on  july  avg partnered with opera software to provide malware security in their web browser opera the protection was added to the existing fraud protection technology netcraft and phishtank from haute secure in july  avg joined forces with israeli company zbang to launch multimi a free windows and ipad app that integrates email social media and multimedia in one interface avg provides linkscanner for the app checking each link that is sent through email shared on a social network or found via search in december  avg and yahoo partnered for the secure search toolbar in september  avg partnered with facebook to launch facebooks privacy application avg crowd control in september  avg partnered with the slovenian company xlab doo to integrate isl online desktop sharing technology into avg business managed workplace  remote monitoring and management software in order to give managed services providers the ability to easily access and control an unlimited number of unattended remote computers in july  avg business cloudcare integrated isl light client this replaced the outgoing remote it product controversyedit in may  avg technologies issued a copyright claim referred to as a takedown request for a youtube video of  pop song never gonna give you up performed by british singer rick astley the video which as of october  has over  million views and  comments had been uploaded in  and was restored within  hours by youtube the videos name refers to the internet meme commonly referred to as rickrolling where someone pranks others by tricking them into going to the video avgs browser addon avg secure search has been criticized as being adware since it is frequently bundled with other software and is often mistakenly installed and exhibits malwarelike behavior avg secure search is also advertised to users of the free versions of avg products although the addon offers legitimate malwareblocking capabilities the default behavior of changing the internet browsers default search engine homepage and new tab page to avg secure search is reminiscent of a potentially unwanted program pup problems uninstalling the addon have been widely reported and the addon could potentially make an internet browser more vulnerable to attacks referencesedit  a b c avg technologies nv financial statements google retrieved  june    avg surpasses  million users worldwide nowavgcom retrieved  march    a b avast acquires antivirus maker avg for bn to gain scale and dive into iot security techcrunch    a b avast closes acquisition of avg technologies september     grisoft celebrates  years of internet security success avg technologies bulletin  december  avgcom  december  retrieved  november    intel buys part of grisoft grisoftcom  september  retrieved  november    intel buys part of avg technologies avgcom  september  retrieved  november    avg technologies announces release of ewido antispyware avgcouk  june  retrieved  november    grisoft announces release of ewido antispyware avgukcom  june  archived from the original on  september  retrieved  november    microsoft incorporates avg into the vista security center avgukcom archived from the original on  september  retrieved  november    whats new in gfi mailsecurity for exchangesmtp  kbasegficom retrieved  november  permanent dead link  avg acquires exploit pre