eveloped antivirus software and internet security services such as avg antivirus and has corporate offices in europe israel brazil canada and the united states as of  february  over  million active users used avgs software products and services which include internet security performance optimization and personal privacy and identity protection applications in july  avast software announced that it intends to acquire avg the acquisition was completed on september   and avast and avg operate as a single company since october   retaining the two separate brands contents  history  products  multiplatform windows android mac  android security  productivity  mac security  productivity  privacy  business security  partnerships  controversy  references  external links historyedit company was founded in brno czech republic by jan gritzbach and tomáš hofer in  as grisoft c software spol s r o it was owned by jan gritzbach in  jan gritzbach decided to sell grisoft to benson oak capital acquisitions holding company grisoft inc based in wilmington delaware was used for the transaction in  the company was renamed to grisoft sro three years later benson oak sold a  share in the company to intel capital and enterprise investors for us million holding company was grisoft holdings bv based in amsterdam netherlands later grisoft international bv that gradually became the main company on  april  grisoft acquired the german company ewido networks an antispyware software manufacturer and incorporated ewidos features into new versions of avg software on  november  microsoft announced that avg security products would be available directly from the windows security center in windows vista since  june  the avg software has also been used as an optional component of gfi mailsecurity produced by gfi software on  december  grisoft announced the acquisition of exploit prevention labs developer of the linkscanner safe surfing technology in  grisoft sro was renamed to avg technologies cz sro and grisoft international bv to avg technologies nv this change was made to increase the effectiveness of their marketing activities in january  avg announced their plans to acquire sana security were finalized plans to integrate sanas technologies in their free consumer product avg antivirus are still under consideration according to jr smith avgs chief executive sana securitys developed technologies are currently licensed to symantec on  october  ta associates announced that they bought a minority stake in avg technologies for more than us million on april  avg announced the appointed of security industry veteran yuval benitzhak as senior vice president of engineering benitzhak became the chief technology officer later that year on  june  avg announced the acquisition of north carolinabased walling data a north america security software distribution that has distributed avg offerings across the united states since  on  november  avg announced the acquisition of tel avivbased droidsecurity a company that specializes in the field of mobile security solutions for android devices upon completion of the acquisition droidsecurity will become a wholly owned subsidiary of avg and droidsecurity ceo and cofounder eran pfeffer will become the general manager of avg’s mobile solutions team in december  avg released a mandatoryinstall update to the  version of its antivirus software which caused thousands of  bit windows vista and windows  computers to become completely inoperable avg has since released a fix which attempts to repair computers bricked after installing the update affected users can watch the following video on avgs official youtube page to resolve the issue on  january  a dangerous rogue appeared the interface and graphics resemble the previous version of the software and uses sophisticated social engineering to deceive users and infect their systems the malware also contains the internet explorer emergency mode on  december  avg technologies announced its acquisition of bsecure technologies inc bsecure a leading provider of proprietary cloudbased technology in the internet filtering industry since  and the most endorsed software provider for family online safety in  the group was restructured again avg technologies holdings bv was founded having avg technologies cz sro and avg technologies nv as its subsidiaries on  february  avg technologies nv was listed on new york stock exchange on  june  avg technologies announced the acquisition of level platforms march   jr smith ceo tendered his resignation from avg after eight years as ceo and leading the company to a successful ipo on the nyse and delivering eight quarters of successive highgrowth on  july  avg technologies announced gary kovacs as the companys new ceo in november  avg technologies announced the acquisition of norman safeground asa an oslobased company known for their norman suite of security products avg technologies announced in may  the acquisition of privax a uk based company which is an owner of hidemyass vpn service in september  the company announced the acquisition of location labs a company with personal security products on all four major us cellular carriers on  july  avast software announced that it intended to acquire avg technologies for a purchase price of  per share in cash for a total of around  billion the acquisition was completed on september   and avast and avg operate as a single company as of monday october   the company was delisted from the new york stock exchange productsedit main article avg software multiplatform windows android macedit avg antivirus free avg internet security avg tuneup avg driver updater avg ultimate android security  productivityedit avg antivirus for android avg cleaner for android family products of avgs location labs att smart limits att familymap verizon familybase tmobile familywhere sprint family locator sprint mobile controls mac security  productivityedit avg antivirus for mac avg cleaner for mac privacyedit h